    ('When fifteen-year-old Jacob Lau is pulled from the crumpled remains of his mother''s car, no one can explain why he was driving or why the police can''t find his mother''s body. A beautiful and mysterious neighbor offers to use her unique abilities to help him find his mom. But in exchange she requires Jacob to train as a Soulkeeper, a protector of human souls. He agrees to her demands, desperate for any clue to the mystery of his mother''s disappearance. But soon Jacob finds himself trapped in a web of half-truths, and questions her motives for helping him.','1st Edition','Paperback','9.78146E+12',308,3.71,14458,'The Soulkeepers','https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1308260933l/10897866.jpg','b1317',30.7),
