    ('Six months ago, Crossbones kidnapped the Red Skull''s daughter, Sin, from a government re-education facility and disappeared into the night. Now, he and his spawn of infinite evil have come to the American Midwest to tear a new hole in A.I.M. - but none of them counted on Cap and Agent 13 stumbling into the mix.Collecting: Captain America 15-21','Complete Collection','Paperback','9.78079E+12',216,4.0,953,'Captain America: Red Menace','https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1524855406l/9884768.jpg','b3437',17.42),
    ('There is something strange about Coraline''s new home. It''s not the mist, or the cat that always seems to be watching her, nor the signs of danger that Miss Spink and Miss Forcible, her new neighbours, read in the tea leaves. It''s the other house - the one behind the old door in the drawing room. Another mother and father with black-button eyes and papery skin are waiting for Coraline to join them there. And they want her to stay with them. For ever. She knows that if she ventures through that door, she may never come back.','Special Edition','Paperback','9.78141E+12',192,4.04,393871,'Coraline','https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1392050283l/20764916.jpg','b3438',25.25),
    ('Since publication of the first edition in 1918, A History of the Christian Church by Williston Walker has enjoyed outstanding success and recognition as a classic in the field. Written by an eminent theologian, it combines in its narrative a rare blend of clarity, unity, and balance. In light of significant advances in scholarship in recent years, extensive revisions have been made to this fourth edition. Three scholars from Union Theological Seminary in New York have incorporated new historical discoveries and provided fresh interpretations of various periods in church history from the first century to the twentieth. The result is a thoroughly updated history which preserves the tenor and structure of Walker''s original, unparalleled text.','4th','Hardcover','9.78068E+12',768,3.78,139,'A History of the Christian Church','https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1344401818l/770143.jpg','b3439',44.26),
